  <!-- BOOKING PROCESS — unique content -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px;">What Happens After an Arrest in Washington County?</h2>
      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.75;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">When someone is arrested in Washington County, they are transported to the Washington County Correctional Facility at 611 SW Adams Boulevard in Bartlesville for booking. The booking process includes identity verification, a health assessment, inventory of personal belongings, fingerprinting, and a booking photograph. Charges are entered into the system, warrant status is reviewed, and bail is set according to the court's bond schedule. The facility serves a population area of approximately 52,455 residents across Washington County's seven-state-region communities.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Once bail is set, a family member or friend can contact Angel Bail Bonds at (405) 614-3000 to begin the release process. We verify the inmate's information and bail amount directly with the Washington County Correctional Facility at (918) 332-4011. After paperwork is completed — which can be done entirely by phone or e-sign — we post bail at the facility. The jail then begins release processing, which typically takes 1-2 hours. Distance from Stillwater to Bartlesville is approximately 95 miles or 1 hour 47 minutes by car, which many families appreciate when managing detention facility logistics.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Washington County accepts cash, money orders, and credit cards for direct cash bail payments. However, most families choose to work with a bail bondsman because posting the full cash bail amount is significantly more expensive. With Angel Bail Bonds, you pay a competitive premium rather than the full bail amount, and we handle all the logistics with the jail and court. We accept Zelle and Venmo in addition to traditional payment methods, making the bail process flexible and accessible.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT WASHINGTON COUNTY — unique local content -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px;">About Washington County, Oklahoma</h2>
      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.75;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Washington County is located in northeastern Oklahoma, approximately 95 miles and 1 hour 47 minutes north of Stillwater. The county seat is Bartlesville, Oklahoma, a city of approximately 40,000 people known as the home of Phillips Petroleum (now ConocoPhillips) headquarters. The county has a total population of approximately 52,455 residents spread across picturesque communities in the rolling hills of northeastern Oklahoma.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Bartlesville is a major commercial and cultural hub featuring the iconic Price Tower, designed by renowned architect Frank Lloyd Wright, and the Woolaroc Museum, a world-class art and wildlife facility. The city sits at the intersection of US-60 and US-75, providing accessibility from throughout the region. Law enforcement activity in Washington County includes traffic stops along major state routes, commercial district incidents in downtown Bartlesville, and arrests at the various state and local establishments that serve the county's substantial daytime population influx from surrounding areas.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Other communities in Washington County include Dewey, Copan, Ochelata, Ramona, Vera, Wann, and Lenapah — all charming rural towns with historical significance to northeastern Oklahoma. The county's economy is historically tied to petroleum and energy production, though it has diversified in recent decades. Angel Bail Bonds has served Washington County families for over 15 years and maintains strong working relationships with the Washington County Sheriff's Office and court system.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Communities We Serve in Washington County</h3>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 14px;">
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Bartlesville</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Dewey</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Copan</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Ochelata</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Ramona</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Vera</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Wann</span>
        <span style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-200); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate-700);">Lenapah</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INMATE SEARCH — GEO citability -->
  <section style="padding: 40px 1.5rem; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px;" id="inmate-search">How to Find an Inmate in Washington County Jail</h2>
      <div style="background: var(--slate-50); border-left: 4px solid var(--blue); padding: 20px 24px; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin-bottom: 20px;">
        <p style="color: var(--slate-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75;">
          <strong>To search for an inmate at the Washington County Correctional Facility, call the facility directly at (918) 332-4011 or contact the Washington County Sheriff's Office at (918) 338-4001.</strong> The facility maintains a current roster of all inmates with booking dates, charges, and bond information. You can also sign up for Oklahoma VINE (Victim Information and Notification Everyday) to receive custody status alerts by email or phone. If you cannot locate someone, call Angel Bail Bonds at (405) 614-3000 and we will look them up for you free of charge.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ — compact accordion -->
  <section style="padding: 40px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">Frequently Asked Questions — Washington County Bail Bonds</h2>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;">
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How do I bail someone out of Washington County Jail in Bartlesville?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Call Angel Bail Bonds at (405) 614-3000 any time, day or night. We verify charges and bail with Washington County Correctional Facility at (918) 332-4011, handle all paperwork remotely, and post bail. Most releases take 1-2 hours after bond is posted.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How much does a bail bond cost in Washington County?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Angel Bail Bonds offers competitive rates on Washington County bail bonds. The exact premium depends on the bail amount set by the court. We accept cash, Visa, Mastercard, Zelle, and Venmo, and offer financing for larger bonds. Call (405) 614-3000 for a free quote.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">What are the visiting hours at Washington County Jail?</summary>
